    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We want to favor an \"as you type search\" experience for latin alphabets. The issue here (which we believe is not specific to Samsung but affects all Android IMEs) is that with predictive text enabled, inputs are sent as composition events instead of direct change events. The workflow we implemented to account for indirect composition breaks our intended experience in this case.\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6009 we're reverting the default behaviour to accept all input events (change and composition) by default, with an option to prevent composition from updating the state if customers are in a relevant use-case (ie: non-latin dataset).",
    "created_at": "2024-01-22T13:58:46Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5986#issuecomment-1904061273",
    "id": 1904061273,
